                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The list of persons present is taken from Leahy’s Diary, which notes that the
                    party of fourteen included also a group of British officials not identified by
                    name. The time is from Hull’s engagement calendar. The only record found of the
                    subject of discussion is the following note in Leahy’s Diary: “The general
                    conversation at dinner was about the war and post-war prospects.” (Leahy
                    Papers)</p>
            </div>
